name: robe, dragon
creator: null
description: Chinese dragon robe (ch'i-fu): presented to William John Brinsden (horse cab driver) after he rescued a young Chinese man who fell from a ship into Auckland harbour, circa late 1890s.  Some months later someone came to his door and presented the robe as a gift of thanks from the family of the young man.; ; Note: a ch'ao-fu is a formal garment consisting of two parts, an upper hip length riding style coat, and a lower paired overlapping skirt. It was worn only for important sacrificial ceremonies and rituals by members of the Imperial family and high ranking officials.; A ch'i-fu (dragon robe) was worn for all other court occasions and official duties. It is a full length, right front, side fastening garment.; See Margery Blackman, "Emperor's Court to Village Festival" Otago Museum catalogue, 1998, p.6. (L.J. July 00)
material_tran: 丝绸（纺织品）/AAT材料；金属线/纤维/AAT材料
description_tran: 中国龙袍：约19世纪90年代末，威廉·约翰·布林斯登（马车司机）救下一名从船上掉进奥克兰港的年轻中国男子后赠送给他。几个月后，有人来到他的门前，把这件长袍作为年轻人家人的感谢礼物；注：曹服是一种正式的服装，由两部分组成，一件上齐臀的骑衣和一条下叠裙。它只在重要的祭祀仪式和皇室成员和高级官员的仪式上佩戴。；龙袍是所有其他宫廷场合和公务所穿的。这是一件全长、右前、侧扣的衣服。；参见Margery Blackman，“皇帝的宫廷到乡村的节日”，奥塔哥博物馆目录，1998年，第6页。（L.J.7月00日）

name: Scales
creator: null
material: wood/plant material/AAT Materials; bone/AAT Materials; steel/iron alloy/metal/inorganic material/AAT Materials; string (fiber product)/cord (fiber product)/AAT Materials
description: Encased Chinese scale set. Chinese scale set consisting of a circular steel tray, metal weight, suspension strings and a beam which is made from bone or tooth and has carved graduations along its length. This complete set is stored inside a specially made wooden case shaped like a violin and a handle that tapers in towards the base. The case is halved and space inside hollowed out to fit the different scale components. The narrow base of the case has a cylindrical metal part inserted right through both halves that acts a hinge so the two halves of the case can slide open and closed. The case is further secured with ring that has been woven from a thick fibre, it slides up the handle until it is tight around the thicker part of the handle, thus holding the two halves together. These scales would have been used to weigh small scale items such as powders, herbs etc. These scales and others like it would have come to Samoa through the waves of Chinese settlers and indentured labourers in the mid 18th century to the mid 19th century.
material_tran: 木材/植物材料/AAT材料；骨/AAT材料；钢/铁合金/金属/无机材料/AAT材料；细绳（纤维制品）/绳索（纤维制品
description_tran: 附中文刻度盘。中国的磅秤由一个圆形钢托盘、金属砝码、吊绳和一根由骨头或牙齿制成的横梁组成，横梁上有刻度。这套套装存放在一个特制的木箱内，木箱形状像小提琴，把手朝底座逐渐变细。表壳被减半，内部空间被挖空，以适应不同比例的组件。外壳的狭窄底座有一个圆柱形金属部件，正好插入两半，充当铰链，使外壳的两半可以滑动打开和关闭。表壳进一步用厚纤维编织的环固定，它沿着手柄向上滑动，直到紧紧围绕手柄的较厚部分，从而将两半固定在一起。这些磅秤将用于称量粉末、草药等小规模物品。这些磅秤和其他类似的磅秤将在18世纪中期至19世纪中期通过中国定居者和契约劳工的浪潮来到萨摩亚。

name: shrine
creator: null
material: plastic/organic material/AAT Materials; wood/plant material/AAT Materials
description: Good Luck Shrine; a red painted Chinese Buddhist shrine decorated with gold painted, moulded plastic fish, dragons, lions and bowls of fruit. The structure consists on a raised base with balustrade to sides, at the back is created an alcove with sloping roof. At the front of the alcove are two pillars, one either side adorned with golden dragons. Behind these are mirrors with Chinese characters in gold, glued to their surfaces, as well as one above the alcove. At the back of the alcove is a thin metal panel with printed coloured illustration incorporating a seated figure with staff and bird, dragons, lanterns, birds, bowls of fruit and Chinese characters.; Hanging on either side of the front pillars are pink lanterns with red tassels and inside each a red light. Another red light sits atop the central roof. Atop the side parts of the roof are golden fish. Golden lions sit either side at the front of the balustrade, below these are painted plastic floral relief. At the very front of the base are golden relief of fruit bowls with fruit.; Sitting on the base of the shrine is a melamine plate and bowl, each decorated with red floral design and Chinese characters. Included with the shrine is a packet of incense sticks with printed coloured label showing an illustration of Buddha.; ; base of plate and bowl, moulded text: TONG YA / Melamine Ware / No.768 / 120c; printed text on incense label: CHAN LUEN HING / DEALER IN / BEST QUALITY JOSS STICK; plus numerous Chinese characters on all the objects
material_tran: 塑料/有机材料/AAT材料；木材/植物材料/AAT材料
description_tran: 好运神社；一座红色的中国佛教圣地，上面装饰着金色的模制塑料鱼、龙、狮子和水果碗。该结构由一个凸起的底座组成，底座两侧有栏杆，背面有一个倾斜屋顶的壁龛。壁龛的前面有两根柱子，两边各有一根饰有金龙的柱子。在这些镜子的后面是一面金色的镜子，上面粘着汉字，还有壁龛上方的一面。壁龛后面是一块薄金属板，上面印着彩色插图，上面有一个坐着的人，上面有杖和鸟、龙、灯笼、鸟、水果碗和汉字。；前立柱两侧悬挂着带红色流苏的粉红色灯笼，每个灯笼内部都有一盏红灯。中央屋顶上还有一盏红灯。屋顶的侧面是金鱼。金色的狮子坐在栏杆前面的两侧，下面是彩绘的塑料花卉浮雕。底座的最前面是金色的水果碗浮雕，上面有水果。；坐在神社基座上的是一个三聚氰胺盘子和碗，每个盘子和碗上都装饰着红色的花卉图案和汉字。神社内有一包香，上面印有彩色标签，上面有佛像的插图；盘子和碗的底座，模制文字：TONG YA/三聚氰胺制品/768/120c；熏香标签上的印刷文字：陈/DEALER IN/BEST QUALITY JOSS STICK；加上所有物体上的大量汉字

name: Pulou
creator: null
material: wood/plant material/AAT Materials; pandanus (leaf)/leaf (plant material)/plant material/AAT Materials; [bamboo]/grass/plant material/AAT Materials; [wool textile]/AAT Materials; elastic/trimming (material)/AAT Materials
description: Pulou. Hat. This a handwoven pulou. The brim of this pulou is made of a thin piece of wood that has been curved to form a large circle. On the inside of the brim is a series of three circles made of ofe (bamboo), each decreasing in size the closer they are to the crown. The four circular pieces that make up the brim are connected by four strips of ofe that connect at the tip of the crown. This frame forms a conical shape reminiscent of Chinese origin. The frame is then covered with strips of ofe that have been woven using a cross-hatching technique. The frame is also covered roughly by strips of pandanus to cover the small holes between the woven ofe. The outer surface of the pulou has been stained a dark brown, nearly black, colour. The underside of the pulou reveals the true brown colour of the materials used as well as the weaving techniques used to create it. Where the crown meets the brim is yet another circle of woven bamboo that is attached perpendicular to the pulou. This circle acts as a headband that allows the conical pulou to sit comfortably on the wearers head. Attached also to the underside of the pulou are two chinstraps. The smaller of the two straps is made of a black elastic string. While the larger of the two straps is made of wool that has been fili (braided) using a fili lua (two ply braid) technique. This pulou is indicative of the migration of Chinese to Samoa in the late 1800's. A pulou such as this would have been worn as protection from both the sun and rain.
material_tran: 木材/植物材料/AAT材料；pandanus（叶子）/叶子（植物材料）/植物材料/AAT材料；[竹子]/草/植物材料/AAT材料；[羊毛纺织品]/AAT材料；弹性/修整（材料）/AAT材料
description_tran: 普楼。帽子这是手工制作的pulou。这个铺楼的边缘是由一块弯曲成一个大圆的薄木头制成的。帽沿内侧是一系列由ofe（竹子）制成的三个圆圈，每个圆圈的大小都随着距离王冠越近而减小。构成帽檐的四个圆形部分由四条ofe连接，这些ofe连接在牙冠的尖端。这个框架形成了一个圆锥形，让人想起中国的起源。然后用交叉影线技术编织的ofe条覆盖框架。框架也大致被露兜带覆盖，以覆盖编织的ofe之间的小孔。蒲楼的外表面被染成了深棕色，几乎是黑色。蒲楼的底面展示了所用材料的真正棕色以及制作它的编织技术。在顶部与边缘相接的地方是另一圈垂直于蒲楼的竹编。这个圆圈起到了头带的作用，可以让圆锥形的pulou舒适地坐在佩戴者的头上。附在下面的pulou是两个下巴背带。两条带子中较小的一条是由黑色松紧带制成的。而较大的一条则是用两层编织技术编织的羊毛。这件披风标志着19世纪末中国人迁移到萨摩亚。像这样的披风可以用来防晒和防雨。

name: bowl
creator: null
description: blue and white bowl Seto, dimpled with white glaze, blue flowers and fruit decoration inner with blocks of Chinese characters. outer with scenic decoration in blue.; ; The word in the middle (the famous Chinese character!): Good Fortune; ; Words on the side:; Walking through the Tombs of 5 emperors; The straight treasured sword; Departed from the Minister; Given as a gift for life.; ; From Heart; The Wild goose flew across; The busy town covered in frost; Why the old town is silent like a reed leaf whistle; ; translatted by Bevan (Ms.) Chuang Ka Yan, 23 July 2007; ; the bottom of it just says "Made in the Great Japan" as many older Japanese ceramics would call themselves, "THE GREAT JAPAN"
description_tran: 蓝白相间的濑户碗，酒窝上有白色的釉料，蓝色的花朵和水果装饰内部有汉字块。外面有蓝色的风景装饰；中间的单词（著名的汉字！）：好运；侧面的文字：；走过五位皇帝的陵墓；笔直的宝剑；离开部长；作为生命的礼物；发自内心；大雁飞过；繁忙的小镇被霜覆盖；为什么老城像芦叶哨子一样寂静；庄家燕译，2007年7月23日；它的底部只写着“大日本制造”，就像许多古老的日本陶瓷自称“大日本”一样

name: suona
creator: null
material: wood/plant material/AAT Materials; brass (alloy)/copper alloy/nonferrous metal/metal/inorganic material/AAT Materials
description: musette, Chinese, wood undulating body with six open holes and open thumb hole, brass bell and head with two discs; ; 1   shawm;    maker unknown, China, date unknown;    wood, brass, overall length 432 mm;    1998.60.233   Castle 361 (presented George 1961); ; ;    This instrument, also known as a sona, was used in funeral ceremonies.; ;    The shawm family of instruments dates back to the ancient civilisations of the Middle East and Europe. All shawms, like the modern oboe, have double reeds. Mainly played in pairs, they produce a strident buzzing tone.
material_tran: 木材/植物材料/AAT材料；黄铜（合金）/铜合金/有色金属/金属/无机材料/AAT材料
description_tran: musette，中国，木制波浪形身体，有六个开口孔和拇指开口孔，黄铜钟和头，有两个圆盘；1肖姆；制造商未知，中国，日期未知；木材，黄铜，总长度432毫米；1998.60.233城堡361（乔治1961年赠送）；这种乐器也被称为sona，用于葬礼仪式；shawm乐器家族可以追溯到中东和欧洲的古代文明。所有的棚屋，就像现代双簧管一样，都有双簧片。它们主要成对演奏，发出刺耳的嗡嗡声。

description: dragon robe, cotton and silk woven damask. Large dark blue robe. Fine silk weave with complete replica of dragon pattern in grey silk damask weave. [Manchu] Cuffs, facing at neck etc in damask weave. Striped arm bands, hoof cuffs.; Note: a ch'ao-fu is a formal garment consisting of two parts, an upper hip length riding style coat, and a lower paired overlapping skirt. It was worn only for important sacrificial ceremonies and rituals by members of the Imperial family and high ranking officials.; A ch'i-fu (dragon robe) was worn for all other court occasions and official duties. It is a full length, right front, side fastening garment.; See Margery Blackman, "Emperor's Court to Village Festival" Otago Museum catalogue, 1998, p.6. (L.J. July 00)

description_tran: 龙袍，棉布和丝绸编织的锦缎。大的深蓝色长袍。精细的丝绸编织，完全复制了灰色丝绸锦缎编织中的龙纹。[满语]锦缎编织的袖口、颈部正面等。条纹臂章，蹄铐。；注：曹服是一种正式的服装，由两部分组成，一件上齐臀的骑衣和一条下叠裙。它只在重要的祭祀仪式和皇室成员和高级官员的仪式上佩戴。；龙袍是所有其他宫廷场合和公务所穿的。这是一件全长、右前、侧扣的衣服。；参见Margery Blackman，“皇帝的宫廷到乡村的节日”，奥塔哥博物馆目录，1998年，第6页。（L.J.7月00日）

description: robe, dragon, blue gauze embroidered in silk and gold thread, striped sleeves and hoof cuffs Note: a ch'ao-fu is a formal garment consisting of two parts, an upper hip length riding style coat, and a lower paired overlapping skirt. It was worn only for important sacrificial ceremonies and rituals by members of the Imperial family and high ranking officials. A ch'i-fu (dragon robe) was worn for all other court occasions and official duties. It is a full length, right front, side fastening garment. See Margery Blackman, "Emperor's Court to Village Festival" Otago Museum catalogue, 1998, p.6. (L.J. July 00)

name: sheng
creator: null
material: bamboo/grass/plant material/AAT Materials; wood/plant material/AAT Materials; bone/AAT Materials
description: sheng, Chinese, seventeen bamboo pipes fitted to wooden base (windchest), with oval mouthpiece, bone mouthpiece and ends to two top pipes; ; 1   sheng;    maker unknown, China, date unknown;    bamboo, wood, ivory, 419 x 74 x 124 mm;    1998.60.325   Castle 477a; ; ;    The sheng or hand mouth organ is vital to the development of the western reed organ. Developed by the Han Chinese (206 BC - AD 220) it is defined by the bowl-shaped reed chamber  usually made of wood or metal and blow pipe with seventeen pipes arranged in an incomplete circle; ;    Examples unearthed in archaeological digs have similar arrangements of pipes but the number  may vary. By the time of the Tang dynasty (AD 618 - 907) the form had changed considerably. Period sources describe the sheng as having seventeen pipes suggesting a standardisation.; ;    In the 1950s attempts were made to improve the instrument with experiments ranging from 21 to 36 pipes and a new key technology. In general the 17-pipe instrument still prevails.; ;    The sheng remains the most important part of the modern Chinese orchestra as wells as its use now as a solo instrument.
material_tran: 竹/草/植物材料/AAT材料；木材/植物材料/AAT材料；骨/AAT材料
description_tran: 笙，中国人，十七根竹管，木底座（风箱），有椭圆形吹口，骨吹口，端至两根上管；1胜；制造商未知，中国，日期未知；竹、木、象牙，419 x 74 x 124毫米；1998.60.325城堡477a；笙管或手口管对西方芦苇管的发展至关重要。它由汉族人（公元前206年-公元220年）发展而来，定义为通常由木材或金属制成的碗状芦苇室和十七根管子排列成不完整的圆形的吹管；考古挖掘中出土的例子有类似的管道排列，但数量可能有所不同。到了唐朝（公元618-907年），这种形式发生了很大的变化。时代资料描述笙有十七根管子，暗示着标准化；20世纪50年代，人们试图通过21到36根管道的实验和一项新的关键技术来改进仪器。总的来说，17管乐器仍然占主导地位；笙仍然是现代中国管弦乐队中最重要的组成部分，现在也被用作独奏乐器。

name: Anave
creator: null
description: Anave. Dance club. This is a carved anave made of wood. The anave is a light brown colour with a smooth varnished surface. The handle is cylindrical in shape and undecorated, as is the rest of the anave. The base of the handle is lined with a few thin cracks and a large chip. The handle flares to a collar of triangular nifo (teeth). There are six nifo in total with three on each side of the club. All the nifo are in tact and all have a blunt point. The collar then widens to a flat oval shaped blade. Anave are thought to have been introduced to Samoa and used instead for entertainment purposes as opposed to being used as a foe (paddle) or 'au'upega (weapon of war).
description_tran: Anave。舞蹈俱乐部。这是一个木制雕刻的anave。anave是一种浅棕色，表面光滑。把手是圆柱形的，没有装饰，anave的其余部分也是如此。把手的底部衬有一些薄裂缝和一个大缺口。手柄张开，形成一圈三角形的nifo（牙齿）。总共有六个尼福，俱乐部两边各有三个。所有的尼福都很老练，而且都有一个直率的观点。然后衣领变宽为扁平的椭圆形刀片。Anave被认为是被引入萨摩亚并被用于娱乐目的，而不是被用作敌人（桨）或“au'upega”（战争武器）。

name: vase
creator: null
description: maebyong, stoneware and unglazed typical shape for this type of item - sometimes also referred to as a prunus vase. (kiln ash glazed) Among the most distinctive of shapes in Korean ceramics is the maeby?ng. Developed from the Chinese meiping shape, which is characterised by a straight profile, that narrows at the base and has a trumpet shaped mouth (compare with K2398), the Goryeo maeby?ng developed an S-shaped profile in the early twelfth century. With the decline in influence of Chinese forms, Goryeo kilns began to perfect the elegance of their shapes and the S-shape profile became common. This trend subsequent intensified, so the pronounced S-shaped profile, a shape that does not appear among Chinese meiping in the Song dynasty, can be identified as one of the key innovations of the Goryeo potters. The saucer-shaped mouth is also distinctive. It can be traced to Chinese Tang dynasty (618 - 907 CE) and Five dynasties (907 - 960 CE) bottles. A trumpet-shaped mouth will replace it by th
description_tran: 这类物品的典型形状是梅边、石制品和无釉花瓶，有时也被称为梅花花瓶。（窑灰釉）在韩国陶瓷中最独特的形状之一是maeby？ng.Goryeo maeby由中国的meiping形状发展而来，其特征是直的轮廓，底部变窄，有一个喇叭形的嘴（与K2398相比）？ng在12世纪初形成了S形轮廓。随着中国形式影响力的减弱，高丽窑开始完善其造型的优雅性，S形轮廓变得普遍。这一趋势随后加剧，因此明显的S形轮廓，这种形状在宋代的中国梅平中没有出现，可以被认为是高丽陶工的关键创新之一。碟形的嘴也很有特色。它可以追溯到中国唐朝（公元618-907年）和五代（公元907-960年）的瓶子。一个喇叭形的嘴将取代它

name: Anave
creator: null
description: Anave. Dance club. This is a carved anave made of wood. The anave is a light brown colour with a smooth varnished surface. The handle is cylindrical in shape and undecorated, as is the rest of the anave. The base of the handle is lined with a few thin cracks and a large chip. The handle flares to a collar of triangular nifo (teeth). There are six nifo in total with three on each side of the club. All the nifo are in tact and all have a blunt point. The collar then widens to a flat oval shaped blade. Anave are thought to have been introduced to Samoa and used instead for entertainment purposes as opposed to being used as a foe (paddle) or 'au'upega (weapon of war).
description_tran: Anave。舞蹈俱乐部。这是一个木制雕刻的anave。anave是一种浅棕色，表面光滑。把手是圆柱形的，没有装饰，anave的其余部分也是如此。把手的底部衬有一些薄裂缝和一个大缺口。手柄张开，形成一圈三角形的nifo（牙齿）。总共有六个尼福，俱乐部两边各有三个。所有的尼福都很老练，而且都有一个直率的观点。然后衣领变宽为扁平的椭圆形刀片。Anave被认为是被引入萨摩亚并被用于娱乐目的，而不是被用作敌人（桨）或“au'upega”（战争武器）。

name: vase
creator: null
description: maebyong, stoneware and unglazed typical shape for this type of item - sometimes also referred to as a prunus vase. (kiln ash glazed) Among the most distinctive of shapes in Korean ceramics is the maeby?ng. Developed from the Chinese meiping shape, which is characterised by a straight profile, that narrows at the base and has a trumpet shaped mouth (compare with K2398), the Goryeo maeby?ng developed an S-shaped profile in the early twelfth century. With the decline in influence of Chinese forms, Goryeo kilns began to perfect the elegance of their shapes and the S-shape profile became common. This trend subsequent intensified, so the pronounced S-shaped profile, a shape that does not appear among Chinese meiping in the Song dynasty, can be identified as one of the key innovations of the Goryeo potters. The saucer-shaped mouth is also distinctive. It can be traced to Chinese Tang dynasty (618 - 907 CE) and Five dynasties (907 - 960 CE) bottles. A trumpet-shaped mouth will replace it by th
description_tran: 这类物品的典型形状是梅边、石制品和无釉花瓶，有时也被称为梅花花瓶。（窑灰釉）在韩国陶瓷中最独特的形状之一是maeby？ng.Goryeo maeby由中国的meiping形状发展而来，其特征是直的轮廓，底部变窄，有一个喇叭形的嘴（与K2398相比）？ng在12世纪初形成了S形轮廓。随着中国形式影响力的减弱，高丽窑开始完善其造型的优雅性，S形轮廓变得普遍。这一趋势随后加剧，因此明显的S形轮廓，这种形状在宋代的中国梅平中没有出现，可以被认为是高丽陶工的关键创新之一。碟形的嘴也很有特色。它可以追溯到中国唐朝（公元618-907年）和五代（公元907-960年）的瓶子。一个喇叭形的嘴将取代它

description: guitar, moon, wood, circular, four large faceted wood pegs, scroll-like head, nine upright frets on body, one upright fret on neck, three large painted characters on body left of strings, eight small painted characters between frets, thick cord loop through neck, three thread stings, one broken, one nylon string; ; 1   yueh-ch’in;    maker unknown, China, date unknown;    wood, gut, 565 x 352 x 45 mm;    1998.60.189   Castle 289 (presented, Webb, [1980]); ;    The short-necked, flat backed yueh-ch’in is a member of the lute family and its popular name is the moon guitar.; ;    The Castles later recalled that ‘During the visit of the Chinese Classical Theatre company, a primitive Chinese fiddle came to light in Wellington … Undated, it is a peasant type four-string violin played between the knees, not under the chin. description: vase, maebyong, stoneware, inlaid celadon, pattern of  (unusual) flying cranes in clouds indicates emergence of Koryo over other dynasties. re-built from twelve fragments with new neck Some Chinese inspired motifs gained wide popularity in Korea even though they were not used often in Chinese ceramics. This included the willow, chrysanthemum, crane and bamboo. The most representative of these is the waterfowl among reed and cranes and clouds as seen in this maebyŏng. Cranes and clouds probably derived from Chinese Yue ware. The depiction of such imaginary, fantastic scenes must have appealed to the Goryeo court and aristocracy for whom these ceramics were produced. Korean potters embraced these Chinese designs. The maebyŏng, meaning prunus vase, would have been used as a jug or a wine pot, rather that a vase. Some versions have been found with a small bell shaped lid that indicate they were jars. Some suggest that the shape of a maebyŏng resembles a plum stone. This maebyŏng is pa

description: buyao or hairpin featuring a trembling ornamental end.; long flat silver half round metal pin, with a carved jade bird capped in silver on the end of a spring. Overtop of the spring is mounted a elaborate floral spray featuring tsian tsui or kingfisher feathers in cloisonné and coral and coral beads. A second smaller floral motif is mounted at the base of the jade bird this appears to have been gilt first, but unknown method. From the jade birds beak is attached a chain with a jade cloud shape at end, which in turn has three chains dangling from end with a lotus shape flower. The chain is loop in loop chain.

description_tran: 碗/杯；由瓷器制成。小碗一种小碗，边缘有片状，高的侧面，在一个细的圆形脚上。碗状的白色玻璃内部有细小的裂纹痕迹。外观未上釉，为褐色陶瓷，雕刻装饰为抽象造型和中国文字，雕刻线条内部为黑色油漆。

name: teabowl and saucer
creator: null
description: teabowl and saucer; The teabowl and saucer are made from egg-shell porcelain and enamel paints, the stand is made from wood. The teabowl is small with a circular opening and sits on a thin circular base, the saucer is also circular with faintly raised sides, on a thin circular base. The teabowl and saucer have a white ground and are decorated with polychrome enamel paints in the style of famille rose with boarders in pink and red, with central imagery of quails next to large blue trunk and pink chrysanthemums.; The wooden stand is two parts, the base has a groove for the teabowl to sit in and the back piece has a groove for the saucer to sit in; ; , egg-shell porcelain, famille rose, cup decorated with flowering plants around the outside and patterned border inside rim, saucer features flowering plants in centre and patterned border with four floral medallions,  with wooden stand [no mention of wooden stand on applied arts card or old ethnology cat. card], sticker on applied arts card 'W. Martin Hurst Collection 1138',  both pieces recorded as fine quality' on ethnology cards
material_tran: 陶瓷/陶瓷/无机材料/AAT材料
description_tran: 茶碗和茶托；茶碗和茶托是用蛋壳瓷和搪瓷颜料制成的，支架是用木头制成的。茶碗很小，有一个圆形开口，坐落在一个薄的圆形底座上，茶托也是圆形的，侧面微微凸起，位于一个薄圆形底座上。茶碗和茶托的地面是白色的，用家庭玫瑰风格的多色珐琅颜料装饰，木板是粉红色和红色的，中心意象是鹌鹑，旁边是蓝色的大树干和粉红色的菊花。；木架由两部分组成，底座有一个凹槽供茶碗放置，背板有一个槽供茶托放置，蛋壳瓷、家庭玫瑰、外部装饰有开花植物的杯子和内部边缘的图案边框，茶托的中心有开花植物，边缘有四个花章，有木制支架[应用艺术卡或旧民族学猫卡上没有提到木制支架]，应用艺术卡上的贴纸“W.Martin Hurst Collection 1138”，这两件作品都被记录为优秀的“民族学卡”

description: robe, dragon, man's, dark blue silk with woven design, banded sleeves and hoof cuffs, round neck, banded, side fastening, gilt toggle buttons, centre front and back slit to skirt, unlined.; ; Note: a ch'ao-fu is a formal garment consisting of two parts, an upper hip length riding style coat, and a lower paired overlapping skirt. It was worn only for important sacrificial ceremonies and rituals by members of the Imperial family and high ranking officials.; A ch'i-fu (dragon robe) was worn for all other court occasions and official duties. It is a full length, right front, side fastening garment.; See Margery Blackman, "Emperor's Court to Village Festival" Otago Museum catalogue, 1998, p.6. (L.J. July 00)

description: robe, dragon, man's, dark blue silk with woven design, banded sleeves and hoof cuffs, round neck, banded, side fastening, gilt toggle buttons, centre front and back slit to skirt, unlined.; ; Note: a ch'ao-fu is a formal garment consisting of two parts, an upper hip length riding style coat, and a lower paired overlapping skirt. It was worn only for important sacrificial ceremonies and rituals by members of the Imperial family and high ranking officials.; A ch'i-fu (dragon robe) was worn for all other court occasions and official duties. It is a full length, right front, side fastening garment.; See Margery Blackman, "Emperor's Court to Village Festival" Otago Museum catalogue, 1998, p.6. (L.J. July 00)
description_tran: 长袍，龙，男人的，深蓝色丝绸，编织设计，带袖和蹄袖口，圆领，带条，侧扣，镀金拨动按钮，中央前后开叉到裙子，无衬里；注：曹服是一种正式的服装，由两部分组成，一件上齐臀的骑衣和一条下叠裙。它只在重要的祭祀仪式和皇室成员和高级官员的仪式上佩戴。；龙袍是所有其他宫廷场合和公务所穿的。这是一件全长、右前、侧扣的衣服。；参见Margery Blackman，“皇帝的宫廷到乡村的节日”，奥塔哥博物馆目录，1998年，第6页。（L.J.7月00日）

name: I'o 'ava
creator: null
material: kava/root/plant material/AAT Materials; kava/root/plant material/AAT Materials
description: I'o 'ava. Kava root. 'Ava (kava) is the general name for the entire plant, its powdered form, as well as the beverage. I'o 'ava refers to the 'ava root in its entirety before it has been separated into smaller pieces or ground into powder form. 'Ava is usually used in its powdered form mixed with water as a beverage. This is served during 'ava ceremonies or other important chiefly events.; ; The larger i'o 'ava is a light yellow brown in colour with varying shades of brown throughout. It consists of the stem piece and the root which is attached. It is a solid piece of 'ava and is completely dried out and ready to be cut into smaller pieces or ground into powder.; ; The smaller i'o 'ava is a light brown in colour with varying shades of brown throughout. It consists of two stem pieces and the root which is attached. It is a solid piece of 'ava and is completely dried out and ready to be cut into smaller pieces or ground into powder.
material_tran: kava/根/植物材料/AAT材料；卡瓦/根/植物材料/AAT材料
description_tran: 我很高兴。卡瓦根。”Ava（kava）是整个植物、其粉末形式以及饮料的总称。I’o‘ava指的是在将其分离成小块或研磨成粉末之前的‘ava根’的整体。ava通常以粉末形式与水混合用作饮料。这是在阿瓦仪式或其他重要的主要活动中提供的；较大的i'o'ava是一种浅黄棕色，全身有不同深浅的棕色。它由茎片和附着的根部组成。它是一块实心的‘ava’，完全干燥，可以切成小块或磨成粉末；较小的i'o'ava是浅棕色，全身都是不同深浅的棕色。它由两个茎片和连接的根部组成。它是一块实心的“ava”，完全干燥，可以切成小块或磨成粉末。

name: wine pot
creator: null
material: ceramic/inorganic material/AAT Materials; celadon/ceramic glaze/glaze/coating (material)/AAT Materials; iron glaze/ceramic glaze/glaze/coating (material)/AAT Materials
description: wine pot, without cover, stoneware, iron (black) brush decoration of peony flowers and leaves under celadon glaze. With celadon production at its peak, Korean pottered developed a type of ceramics adorned with a peony design, somewhat like the style and technique used in Chinese Cizhou ware. This wine pot is a superb example of brushed peony (possibly posanghwa) flowers and leaf decoration . The design was painted in iron oxide under the celadon glaze, showing that the Korean potter sometimes adapted Chinese motifs without regard for decorative technique. Designs became bigger and bolder, more spontaneous and more energetic. This allowed the potter to paint the surface freely and directly and was similar in style to Korean mural paintings and gave the pieces a softer edge. Most iron painted celadons were fired in an oxidation kiln, as the colour of the glaze tended to turn a brownish yellow as seen in this ewer.
material_tran: 陶瓷/无机材料/AAT材料；青瓷/陶瓷釉/釉料/涂层（材料）/AAT材料；铁釉/陶瓷釉/釉/涂层（材料）/AAT材料
description_tran: 酒壶，无盖，石制，铁（黑）刷饰牡丹花，下青瓷釉。随着青瓷的生产达到顶峰，韩国陶艺家开发出了一种带有牡丹图案的陶瓷，有点像中国磁州瓷器的风格和技术。这个酒壶是一个极好的例子刷牡丹（可能是波桑瓦）花和叶子装饰。该图案是在青瓷釉下用氧化铁绘制的，表明韩国陶工有时会在不考虑装饰技术的情况下采用中国图案。设计变得更大、更大胆、更自然、更有活力。这使陶工能够自由直接地绘制表面，在风格上与韩国壁画相似，并使作品边缘更柔和。大多数铁彩绘青瓷都是在氧化窑中烧制的，因为釉色往往会变成棕黄色。

name: flag
creator: null
description: scarf or handkerchief; rectangular white silk ink printed with Union Jack and message for help in 17 languages: Annamite, Haka, Kachin, lAizo, Karen, Burmese, Malay, Sumatra, Tamil, Chinese, English, French, Jawi, Thai, W. Shan, E. Shan, N. Shan, Bengali; text: Dear Friend, I am an allied figher. I did not come here to do any harm to you who are my friends. I only want to do harm to the Japanese and chase them away from this country as quickly as possible. If you will assist me, my Government will sufficiently reward you when the Japanese are driven away.
description_tran: 围巾或手帕；矩形白色丝绸墨水，印有Union Jack和17种语言的求助信息：安南语、哈卡语、克钦语、lAizo语、克伦语、缅甸语、马来语、苏门答腊语、泰米尔语、汉语、英语、法语、爪哇语、泰语、W.Shan、E.Shan、N.Shan、孟加拉语；文字：亲爱的朋友，我是一名盟军战士。我来这里不是为了伤害你，你是我的朋友。我只想伤害日本人，尽快把他们赶出这个国家。如果你愿意帮助我，当日本人被赶走时，我国政府将给予你足够的奖励。

name: dish
creator: null
description: Porcelain plate, shallow, underglaze powder blue. Powder blue, or soufflé blue, is different in manufacturing from other blue glazes in which the cobalt material is not mixed with the glaze. Instead, it is blown dry onto the raw biscuit by using a piece of gauze stretched over the end of a bamboo tube, then cover with a clear glaze and fire. It results a rich lapis lazuli tone, which may be further embellished with etched designs or gilding.
material_tran: 陶瓷/陶瓷/无机材料/AAT材料；釉/涂层（材料）/AAT材料
description_tran: 瓷盘，浅，釉下粉蓝色。粉蓝或蛋奶酥蓝在制造上与其他蓝色釉料不同，在其他蓝色釉质中，钴材料不与釉料混合。相反，它是用一块纱布在竹筒的末端将其吹干在生饼干上，然后用透明的釉料和火覆盖。它产生了丰富的青金石色调，可以进一步用蚀刻设计或镀金装饰。

name: pot
creator: null
description: pot, ceramic. Cylindrical tripod pot. Three hollow, tall (185mm high) legs are attached to lower quarter of the vessel body. All three legs have elongated slit 80mm long near upper end. One leg has an animal head, possibly a sheep or ram (mammalian) at upper end. The animal face has a projection out each side with fluted edges. A ball of clay inside this leg creates a rattle sound. The vessel has a rounded base and spherical, unrestricted form of lower portion. Topped with wide vertical neck, flaring out slightly at upper edge to round rim. Pot has been painted two colours; upper two-thirds of the body is black, remainder white slip, most has worn off or faded. Two legs have broken and been repaired, one with filler visible.  K2106 written on object.
description_tran: 陶瓷壶。圆柱形三脚架。三个中空、高（185mm高）的支腿连接到船体的下半部。所有三个支腿的上端附近都有80毫米长的细长狭缝。一条腿的上端有一个动物的头，可能是绵羊或公羊（哺乳动物）。动物的脸每侧都有一个突起，边缘有凹槽。这条腿里面的一个粘土球会发出嘎嘎的声音。该容器具有圆形底座和球形、不受限制的下部。顶部有宽的垂直颈部，在上边缘向圆形边缘微微张开。锅被漆成了两种颜色；上身三分之二为黑色，其余为白色，大部分已磨损或褪色。两条腿断了，已经修复，其中一条腿有填充物。K2106写入对象。

name: jar, ginger
creator: null
material: porcelain/ceramic/inorganic material/AAT Materials; wood/plant material/AAT Materials
description: Porcelain ginger jar, lidded, underglaze blue and white, decorated with trees and bamboos. Ginger jars are identified by their high-shoulders, rounded shapes, small mouths, and domed lids that often continue the piece’s exterior decoration all the way up to the finial. Though ginger jars were initially used to store and transport spices, hence their name, the containers (which usually lack handles) have been used chiefly as decorative objects since the 19th century, when demand in the West for Chinese antiques spurred the export of these pieces to Europe, as well as the manufacture of copycat jars in Western pottery centers.

description_tran: 瓷姜缸，有盖，釉下青花，饰以树木和竹子。姜罐的特征是它们的高肩、圆形、小嘴和圆顶盖子，这些盖子通常一直延续着姜罐的外部装饰，直到最后。尽管姜罐最初用于储存和运输香料，因此得名，但自19世纪以来，这些容器（通常没有把手）一直主要用作装饰物，当时西方对中国古董的需求刺激了这些物品出口到欧洲，以及在西方陶器中心制造仿制品罐。

name: jug
creator: null
description: jug, Chinoiserie [Chinese manner] style, ironstone.  The shape of the jug, octagonal, can compare with those made in Stone China dated between circa 1810 to circa 1840 (Lewis, 1985, pp. 142-143). The patent for "Ironstone China" was entered in July 1813 under the name of Charles James Mason of Fenton in the Staffordshire Potteries. the resulting heavy durable body was extensively employed fro dinner or dessert services and was, if freely, painted with colourful "Japan" or other oriental-inspired designs. (Godden, 1974, p. 204, pl. 266-276)
description_tran: 壶，中式风格，铁石。壶的形状是八角形的，可以与1810年至1840年左右在石制中国制造的壶相比较（Lewis，1985，第142-143页）。“Ironstone China”的专利于1813年7月在斯塔福德郡陶器厂以芬顿的查尔斯·詹姆斯·梅森的名义申请。由此产生的厚重耐用的机身被广泛用于晚餐或甜点服务，如果自由的话，还被涂上了五颜六色的“日本”或其他东方风格的设计。（Godden，1974年，第204页，第266-276页）

name: Lohan
creator: null
material: wood/plant material/AAT Materials; stone/rock/inorganic material/AAT Materials
description: Seated Lohan holding pearl, traces of gesso and decoration remaining, missing hand reinstated.  This is one of 260 pieces presented by Captain George A Humphreys-Davies. Humphrey’s-Davies (born circa 1888, England – died December 1948, Cannes, France) was a farmer, collector of Eastern ceramics, jades, bronzes and Japanese prints. Educated at Oxford and served with the 2nd Life Guards in the First World War. Post war he saw service in India before coming to Auckland to farm and live at Freshwater, Kawakawa Bay in the early 1920s. A genuine connoisseur and keenly interest in every phase of art, he became a valued supporter of the activities of Auckland Museum. Through the years he acquired a very fine collection of works of eastern art and presented a collection of Chinese pottery figures to the museum.
material_tran: 木材/植物材料/AAT材料；石头/岩石/无机材料/AAT材料
description_tran: 罗汉坐着，手里拿着珍珠，残留着石膏和装饰的痕迹，失踪的手又恢复了原状。这是乔治·汉弗莱斯·戴维斯上尉赠送的260件作品之一。汉弗莱·戴维斯（约1888年生于英国，1948年12月卒于法国戛纳）是一位农民，收藏东方陶瓷、玉器、青铜器和日本版画。在牛津大学接受教育，并在第一次世界大战中加入第二生命卫队。战后，他在印度服役，20世纪20年代初来到奥克兰，在川川湾淡水农场生活。他是一位真正的鉴赏家，对艺术的各个阶段都非常感兴趣，成为奥克兰博物馆活动的重要支持者。多年来，他收藏了一批非常精美的东方艺术作品，并向博物馆赠送了一批中国陶俑。

name: plate
creator: null
description: plate, 'tumbledown dick'. "Plate, part of a service. Tumbledown dick" pattern, olive green."; Tumbledown Dick was first recorded in about 1820 with pattern number 2987. The pattern is a copy, or close representation, of a Chinese design of the Yung Cheng period (1723 - 1735).; ; The pattern was produced at Spode in many versions. It was often printed and then coloured. It was also printed and then painted with 'ackey' (a water soluble resist) which allowed the pattern to remain unaffected when a subsequent transfer print of a 'sheet pattern' was applied over the whole surface. At the 'washing-off' stage (when the transfer paper is removed) the areas of the transferred sheet pattern which were over the 'ackey' were washed away leaving the outline of the first pattern. This could then be hand coloured after the gloss firing.; ; This technique was used for a number of patterns when a combination of prints was used. Tumbledown Dick was often used with Marble Sheet as in pattern 3716 of 1823.; ; The name Tumbledown Dick was probably a factory or a collectors' name rather than one chosen for marketing purposes. One theory is that the name derives from an upside-down dickie bird!; ; In 1980 Tumbledown Dick was produced as dinnerware on fine stone body and named Prince Regent. It had pattern number W160. This version was probably withdrawn in the late 1980s all the fine stone was discontinued in 1995; ; http://www.spode.co.uk/history/Tumbledown%20Dick.htm
description_tran: 盘子，“滚蛋”。“盘子，服务的一部分。翻滚迪克”图案，橄榄绿。“翻滚的迪克最早记录于1820年，图案编号2987。该图案是中国雍正时期（1723-1735）设计的复制品或近似品；斯波德制作了许多版本的图案。它经常被印刷，然后上色。还对其进行了印刷，然后涂上了“ackey”（一种水溶性抗蚀剂），当随后在整个表面上进行“片状图案”的转印时，该图案不会受到影响。在“冲洗”阶段（当转移纸被移除时），转移的纸张图案在“ackey”上的区域被冲洗掉，留下第一个图案的轮廓。然后可以在光泽烧制后手工上色；当使用印刷品的组合时，这种技术被用于许多图案。翻滚的迪克经常与大理石床单一起使用，如1823年的图案3716所示；“翻滚迪克”这个名字可能是一个工厂或收藏家的名字，而不是出于营销目的而选择的。一种理论认为这个名字来源于一只倒置的小鸟；1980年，“翻滚的迪克”被制作成精美的石头餐具，并被命名为“摄政王子”。它的图案编号为W160。这个版本可能在20世纪80年代末被撤回，所有的细石在1995年停产；http://www.spode.co.uk/history/Tumbledown%20Dick.htm

name: charger
creator: null
material: ceramic/inorganic material/AAT Materials; tin glaze/ceramic glaze/glaze/coating (material)/AAT Materials
description: charger, London delftware, large platter after an original by Bernard Palissy who took the subject from a painting by Titian called 'La Fecondite' pattern with Cutlers Arms and rest. Other examples of the same piece at Godden, 1975, pl. 35; ; marks   recto above central arms on rim ‘I.H’; in cavetto ‘ON/ ISAAC HICKS/ ANNO DOM’ 1650; verso makers mark ‘W.P’; ; This delightful ‘London delftware’ charger 'la fécondité’ is to be made in London around 1658. It is based quite closely on a subject first used in Palissy ware by Bernard Palissy (flourished 1542-62) in France.; ; The central image depicts a reclining woman with five children playing in front of a draped curtain. The high relief is elaborately highlighted in blue, ochre, yellow and green. The recesses around the rim also have individual scenes. In the top center rondel can be seen the alms of the Guild of Cutlers.; ; From the 14th century large qualities of Chinese blue and white porcelain had been sold in Europe. The European potters had been unable to produce the white body necessary for porcelain, and during the 16th century the discovery was made that tin oxide mixed with clear lead glaze produced and opaque white glaze covering the natural brown clays. The surface could then be decorated.; ; charger 'la fecundite series’, London delftware, possibly Southwark, London, England, circa 1675
material_tran: 陶瓷/无机材料/AAT材料；锡釉/陶瓷釉/釉/涂层（材料）/AAT材料
description_tran: 充电器，伦敦三角器，以伯纳德·帕利西的原作命名的大拼盘，帕利西从提香的一幅名为“La Fecondite”的画作中提取了主题，画中有Cutlers Arms和rest。同一件作品的其他例子，Godden，1975年，第35页；在边缘‘I’的中心臂上方做直肠标记。H在洞穴“ON/ISAAC HICKS/ANNO DOM”1650；verso制造商标记“W”。P这款令人愉快的“伦敦德尔夫特”充电器“la fécondité”将于1658年左右在伦敦制造。它非常紧密地基于法国的Bernard Palissy（1542-62年兴盛）首次在Palissy瓷器中使用的主题；中心图像描绘了一位斜倚的妇女和五个孩子在一块垂着的窗帘前玩耍。高浮雕以蓝色、赭色、黄色和绿色精心突出。边缘周围的凹槽也有单独的场景。在最上面的中央可以看到朗德尔的屠夫公会的施舍；从14世纪开始，大量的中国青花瓷在欧洲销售。欧洲的陶工一直无法生产出瓷器所需的白色坯体，在16世纪，人们发现氧化锡与透明的铅釉混合，产生了覆盖在天然棕色粘土上的不透明白色釉。然后可以对表面进行装饰；充电器“la繁殖力系列”，伦敦delftware，可能是英国伦敦南华克，约1675年

name: plate
creator: null
description: plate, 'tumbledown dick'. "Plate, part of a service. Tumbledown dick" pattern, olive green."; Tumbledown Dick was first recorded in about 1820 with pattern number 2987. The pattern is a copy, or close representation, of a Chinese design of the Yung Cheng period (1723 - 1735).; ; The pattern was produced at Spode in many versions. It was often printed and then coloured. It was also printed and then painted with 'ackey' (a water soluble resist) which allowed the pattern to remain unaffected when a subsequent transfer print of a 'sheet pattern' was applied over the whole surface. At the 'washing-off' stage (when the transfer paper is removed) the areas of the transferred sheet pattern which were over the 'ackey' were washed away leaving the outline of the first pattern. This could then be hand coloured after the gloss firing.; ; This technique was used for a number of patterns when a combination of prints was used. Tumbledown Dick was often used with Marble Sheet as in pattern 3716 of 1823.; ; The name Tumbledown Dick was probably a factory or a collectors' name rather than one chosen for marketing purposes. One theory is that the name derives from an upside-down dickie bird!; ; In 1980 Tumbledown Dick was produced as dinnerware on fine stone body and named Prince Regent. It had pattern number W160. This version was probably withdrawn in the late 1980s all the fine stone was discontinued in 1995; ; http://www.spode.co.uk/history/Tumbledown%20Dick.htm
description_tran: 盘子，“滚蛋”。“盘子，服务的一部分。翻滚迪克”图案，橄榄绿。“翻滚的迪克最早记录于1820年，图案编号2987。该图案是中国雍正时期（1723-1735）设计的复制品或近似品；斯波德制作了许多版本的图案。它经常被印刷，然后上色。还对其进行了印刷，然后涂上了“ackey”（一种水溶性抗蚀剂），当随后在整个表面上进行“片状图案”的转印时，该图案不会受到影响。在“冲洗”阶段（当转移纸被移除时），转移的纸张图案在“ackey”上的区域被冲洗掉，留下第一个图案的轮廓。然后可以在光泽烧制后手工上色；当使用印刷品的组合时，这种技术被用于许多图案。翻滚的迪克经常与大理石床单一起使用，如1823年的图案3716所示；“翻滚迪克”这个名字可能是一个工厂或收藏家的名字，而不是出于营销目的而选择的。一种理论认为这个名字来源于一只倒置的小鸟；1980年，“翻滚的迪克”被制作成精美的石头餐具，并被命名为“摄政王子”。它的图案编号为W160。这个版本可能在20世纪80年代末被撤回，所有的细石在1995年停产；http://www.spode.co.uk/history/Tumbledown%20Dick.htm

description: robe, dragon, man's; coiled dragon motif, brown satin embroidered in silk satin stitch, mainly in blues and pinks and gold thread; plain black sleeves, no braiding; Pekin stitch; braid; embroidered in gold thread and multicoloured silk embroidery; gold and black striped sleeves, no collar.; Note: a ch'ao-fu is a formal garment consisting of two parts, an upper hip length riding style coat, and a lower paired overlapping skirt. It was worn only for important sacrificial ceremonies and rituals by members of the Imperial family and high ranking officials.; A ch'i-fu (dragon robe) was worn for all other court occasions and official duties. It is a full length, right front, side fastening garment.; See Margery Blackman, "Emperor's Court to Village Festival" Otago Museum catalogue, 1998, p.6. (L.J. July 00); (possibly riding coat)

description: Porcelain water pot with wooden stand, underglaze blue and white decoration, showing two figures in a landscape. The two figures are designed according to two of the eight immortals, which are legendary beings of Daoism, said to have lived at various times and attained immortality through their studies of nature’s secrets. The Eight Immortals each represent a different condition in life: poverty, wealth, aristocracy, plebeianism, age, youth, masculinity, and femininity. They are popular in Chinese art as altogether they symbolise prosperity and longevity.

name: vase
creator: null
description: stoneware, glaze.; Kerstan first trained as a porcelain painter in industry but was more attracted to clay work than decoration and became an apprentice for well-known German potter, Richard Bampi, an exponent of Asian type glazes. Kerstan became fascinated with the Far East and travelled there many times. He built Germany’s first anagama-style (hillside) kiln in the Black Forest. His major contribution to German ceramics is his combination of a relaxed oriental attitude to making with a strong sense for colourful glazes, drawn from his early days as a glaze specialist.;  The ‘Kaisergelts’ translates as ‘Kaiser’s yellow’ or ‘Imperial Yellow’ and was, in Chinese Ch’ing Dynasty times restricted for the use of the Emperor. There is a German Kaisergrun glaze (Kaiser green) and this name may be his playful take on an established glaze. ‘Eisenfell’ refers to the iron saturated glaze used beneath the yellow.
material_tran: 陶瓷/无机材料/AAT材料；釉/涂层（材料）/AAT材料
description_tran: 石器，釉料。；克斯坦最初在工业界接受瓷器画家的培训，但他更喜欢粘土作品而不是装饰，并成为著名德国陶艺家理查德·班皮的学徒，他是亚洲风格釉料的代表。克斯坦迷上了远东，并多次前往那里。他在黑森林建造了德国第一座anagama风格的（山坡）窑。他对德国陶瓷的主要贡献是，他将东方人轻松的制作态度与他早期担任釉料专家时对彩色釉料的强烈感觉相结合。；“皇帝黄”的翻译是“皇帝的黄”或“帝王黄”，在中国清朝时期，皇帝只能使用它。有一种德国凯撒釉（凯撒绿），这个名字可能是他对一种既定釉的有趣模仿。”Eisenfell是指在黄色下面使用的铁饱和釉。

description: vase, baluster shaped, lidded decorated with adults and children among rocks and banullas, "lidded vase, baluster form, adults and children among rocks and banullas, clear firmly drawn". "To an institution which, like the Auckland Museum, which has to depend so much on the personal efforts of its friends, it is no slight advantage to receive the active sympathy and constant assistance you have granted during many years; and which has always been so appropriately and gracefully tendered." So wrote Thomas Peacock, (President, Auckland Museum) in a letter to James Tannock Mackelvie on 18 August 1881. In 1934, the museum was enriched by the substantial loan of the collection of Auckland businessman, philanthropist and collector, James Tannock Mackelvie (born 1824, Scotland - died 1885, England). This guan or covered jar is an addition to Mackelvie's original collection that has benefited from judicious purchasing by his trustees, based on the spirit of the Mackelvie's original collection.

description: gilded [silver] Chinese- style chatelaine. From the top is a hook which is attached to a crayfish with a clip on its back (which perhaps the original clip). From this is suspended a triangular ribbon filigree foliate medallion with hinged connection below attached to a basket shape created with floral filigree. Below this is a finial with a suspension hoop and two chains attached, this leads to a plaque which is a three dimensional unfurling scroll. This is decorated on both sides with twisted filigree borders, floral designs and [Chinese] characters. Lastly from this four suspension rings are attached with chains and tools at the end. The tools are created with long hollow chenier with a decorative floral ends attached to the chain. Left to right is a spiked tool, a missing tool, another spiked tool and lastly a scoop tool.

name: chatelaine
creator: null
material: silver/nonferrous metal/metal/inorganic material/AAT Materials; [gilt]/gilding (material)/metal/inorganic material/AAT Materials
description: gilded [silver] Chinese- style chatelaine. From the top is a hook which is attached to a crayfish with a clip on its back (which perhaps the original clip). From this is suspended a triangular ribbon filigree foliate medallion with hinged connection below attached to a basket shape created with floral filigree. Below this is a finial with a suspension hoop and two chains attached, this leads to a plaque which is a three dimensional unfurling scroll. This is decorated on both sides with twisted filigree borders, floral designs and [Chinese] characters. Lastly from this four suspension rings are attached with chains and tools at the end. The tools are created with long hollow chenier with a decorative floral ends attached to the chain. Left to right is a spiked tool, a missing tool, another spiked tool and lastly a scoop tool.
material_tran: 银/有色金属/金属/无机材料/AAT材料；镀金/镀金（材料）/金属/无机材料/AAT材料
description_tran: 镀金[银]中式城堡。从顶部是一个钩子，它背上有一个夹子（可能是原来的夹子），挂在小龙虾身上。从这上面悬挂着一个三角形的带状花丝叶片奖章，下面有铰链连接，连接到用花丝制成的篮子形状上。下面是一个带有悬挂环和两条链的装饰，这导致了一个斑块，这是一个三维展开的卷轴。它的两侧都装饰着扭曲的花丝边框、花卉图案和[中国]文字。最后，四个悬挂环用链条和工具连接在末端。这些工具是用长的中空雪尼尔制成的，链上有装饰性的花端。从左到右是一个带尖刺的工具，一个缺失的工具，另一个带尖头的工具，最后是一个勺状工具。

name: platter
creator: null
description: Stoneware, oxidised. Sancai (three colour) glaze.; ; Yasuda has been resident in England for many years and considers himself, ‘an English potter of Japanese origins’. He is highly regarded in England and was the 1995 judge of the Fletcher Challenge Ceramics Award.; ; Yasuda’s use of the ‘sancai’ (three colour) glaze links with historical Chinese pottery from the T’ang Dynasty – the San-Ts’ai. The colours derive from iron and copper and flow in a partly controlled way over the cream glaze base. It was sometimes called ‘egg and spinach’ by early western dealers.
description_tran: 氧化的石器。三彩釉；安田在英国居住多年，他认为自己是“日本血统的英国陶艺家”。他在英国备受推崇，曾是1995年弗莱彻挑战陶瓷奖的评委；安田使用的“三彩”（三色）釉料与中国唐朝的历史陶器——三彩相联系。颜色来源于铁和铜，并以部分受控的方式在奶油釉基底上流动。它有时被早期的西方经销商称为“鸡蛋和菠菜”。

description: robe, dragon, silk, kossu, and gold thread. Woven blue dragon robe with symbols of five clawed dragons, lined with blue silk, black sleeves.; Note: a ch'ao-fu is a formal garment consisting of two parts, an upper hip length riding style coat, and a lower paired overlapping skirt. It was worn only for important sacrificial ceremonies and rituals by members of the Imperial family and high ranking officials.; A ch'i-fu (dragon robe) was worn for all other court occasions and official duties. It is a full lenght, right front, side fastening garment.; Five claw "lung" dragons were worn by the Imperial family and high ranking officials with four claw "mang" dragons on the garments of the lowest ranking officials.; See Margery Blackman, "Emperor's Court to Village Festival" Otago Museum catalogue, 1998, pp.6-7. (L.J. July 00)

The figure is wearing a long red and green tunic with yellow pants. The horse is painted white and is wearing green painted reins and saddle

name: hanging
creator: null
size: Right proper: 3885mm; Left proper: 3900mm; top edge: 3027mm;
description: silk wall hanging. richly embroidered. Chien Ling Period, 4th year.; ; Embroidery is done on a ground of black satin weave silk in several panels, a central piece with a border on each side and a top and bottom. There is evidence that this design may have been much bigger at one stage, with the right hand side (LP) border swallowing some of the design where the panels meet.; There is more evidence throughout where elements are remade and old designs covered. The most obvious of these are the pine(?) flower embroidery at the top is strategically covering large gold Chinese characters.; ; The back is lined with a red fabric. In the central embroidered panel is a figure of a woman with a smaller child to her right. On either side of this are a tiger in a falling position with a man on the outside wrestling another tiger. Above and below this are sets of skinny elephants, two pairs above and one set below. Along the top is two dragons and at the bottom is two animals fighting? With a bird(pheasant?) at the shoulder of the left figure. The background is embroidered all over with bats, clouds and Taoist emblems, nature scenes and at the bottom houses and land.; ; Surrounding this is a border of large Chinese symbols/characters in couched gold thread. Then a border of repeating clouds and suns then a slightly larger border of figures doing things in couched gold thread and silk floss embroidery. There is then another skinny border of a meander pattern. The outside edge is a larger border again, this time of floral designs and scrolls with Chinese text inside. The final edge is a couched gold thread border of about 6 threads.
size_tran: 右侧本体：3885mm；左侧本体：3900mm；顶部边缘：3027mm；
description_tran: 丝绸壁挂。刺绣丰富。乾陵四年；刺绣是在黑色缎面丝绸的地面上进行的，分为几个面板，中间的一块两边都有边框，顶部和底部。有证据表明，这种设计在某个阶段可能要大得多，右手边（LP）的边界吞噬了面板相交处的一些设计。；在元素被重新制作和旧设计被覆盖的地方，有更多的证据。其中最明显的是顶部的松（？）花刺绣，巧妙地覆盖了大大的金色汉字；背面衬有红色布料。在中央的刺绣面板是一个妇女的形象，她的右边有一个较小的孩子。两边是一只老虎，它处于摔倒的姿势，外面有一个人在和另一只老虎摔跤。上面和下面是几对瘦骨嶙峋的大象，上面两对，下面一对。上面是两只龙，下面是两只动物在打架？左图肩上有一只鸟（山鸡？）。背景上绣满蝙蝠、云朵和道教徽章、自然景观以及底部的房屋和土地；围绕着它的是一条用金线编织的大型中国符号/字符的边界。然后是重复的云和太阳的边界，然后是稍微大一点的人物的边界，他们用编织的金线和丝线刺绣做事情。然后是另一个弯曲模式的瘦边界。外侧边缘是一个更大的边界，这一次是花卉设计和卷轴，里面有中文文本。最后的边缘是一个大约有6根线的编织金线边界。

name: chatelaine
creator: null
material: silver/nonferrous metal/metal/inorganic material/AAT Materials; enamel/coating (material)/AAT Materials
description: silver Chinese style chatelaine with suspended tools. A silver chain is looped at the top attached to a double walled medallion with mirrored design back to front, featuring a bat at the top and intertwined circles below, with floral designs either side. These are then decorated with enamel in blue green and purple colour. Below,  five suspension rings are attached with chain lengths and a tool on each end. From left to right, a sword shaped tool with enamel decoration, a scoop with rectangular cut out designs, a tongue scraper featuring double fish motif and bat. A spike tool with rectangular cut out designs and a scimitar shaped tool with enamel designs. One additional tool has been added on to the same link as the sword tool and is another tongue scraper. This has a hallmark and is mostly cut out design with a circle motif in the middle.

description: Figure; Mingqi tomb figure of a Scthian horse rider. Made from a buff earthenware that is unglazed with a white gesso coat and traces of polychrome wash. name: disc
creator: null
description: disc ritual, circlet. Light green / cream-coloured jade. Outer edge has three right angle cut outs, regularly placed. In-between each is a protuberance wheel which has two cuts at regular intervals, with scalloped outer edge, dividing it into three. Surface is ground flat and edges ground. Central hole measures 67x68mm. Crack present front and back from edge to edge. Astronomical object?

name: vase
creator: null
material: ceramic/inorganic material/AAT Materials; celadon/ceramic glaze/glaze/coating (material)/AAT Materials
description: maebyong, stoneware, celadon glaze with incised decoration, an interesting one in the traditional shape used - the sharp contrast of colouring clearly defined. also a very rough pattern is incised on one side - probably based on some variety of water weed. there are also some marks on the outside indicating the roughness of the grave robbers in their probing with steel spikes to find such items. Maeybyong (prunus vase), stoneware. Late KORYO. Yellow celadon glaze. Roughly incised pattern on one side. Damage on one side was probably from steel probes used by the grave robbers. [gallery card] This maebyŏng has a very immediate single incised design of a lotus blossom. Freely composed, it follows the contours of the vase and balances the surrounding empty space with a graceful rendering of the flowers stems and leaves. Such individuality has produced an appealing and naturalistic effect. The maebyŏng has a repaired hole in its shoulder. When collectors’ interest in Korean wares intens
material_tran: 陶瓷/无机材料/AAT材料；青瓷/陶瓷釉/釉料/涂层（材料）/AAT材料
description_tran: 梅边，石器，青瓷釉与雕刻装饰，一个有趣的一个在传统的形状使用-色彩的鲜明对比清楚地定义。还有一个非常粗糙的图案刻在一边——可能是基于某种水草。外面也有一些痕迹，表明盗墓者在用钢钉寻找这些物品时的粗鲁。梅瓶，石制品。KORYO迟到了。黄色青瓷釉。一侧有粗糙的切割图案。一侧的损坏可能来自盗墓者使用的钢制探针。[画廊卡]这张maeby??ng有一个非常直接的莲花单刻设计。它构图自由，遵循花瓶的轮廓，以优美的花茎和叶子来平衡周围的空地。这种个性产生了一种吸引人的自然主义效果。maeby??ng的肩部有一个修复过的洞。当收藏者对韩国商品的兴趣日益浓厚

name: platter
creator: null
description: Stoneware, oxidised. Sancai (three colour) glaze.; ; Yasuda has been resident in England for many years and considers himself, ‘an English potter of Japanese origins’. He is highly regarded in England and was the 1995 judge of the Fletcher Challenge Ceramics Award.; ; Yasuda’s use of the ‘sancai’ (three colour) glaze links with historical Chinese pottery from the T’ang Dynasty – the San-Ts’ai. The colours derive from iron and copper and flow in a partly controlled way over the cream glaze base. It was sometimes called ‘egg and spinach’ by early western dealers.
description_tran: 氧化的石器。三彩釉；安田在英国居住多年，他认为自己是“日本血统的英国陶艺家”。他在英国备受推崇，曾是1995年弗莱彻挑战陶瓷奖的评委；安田使用的“三彩”（三色）釉料与中国唐朝的历史陶器——三彩相联系。颜色来源于铁和铜，并以部分受控的方式在奶油釉基底上流动。它有时被早期的西方经销商称为“鸡蛋和菠菜”。

Dark blue cotton lining.; ; Tsuba (sword guards) were used to protect the sword wielder's hands from sliding onto the blade. They are usually finely decorated, incorporating traditional motifs and designs and made from a variety of metals, such as iron, steel, brass or shakudo - an alloy of copper and gold.

description: Ginger jar; Made from porcelain, wood, and enamel paint. The jar has a circular opening and rounded shoulders, an ovoid body and a circular base. The jar has a wooden lid carved like a seedpod with open work. The body of the jar is decorated with polychrome enamels showing four circular medallions of flowers, scholar wares and fo lion in a garden . Two half-floral decorations on the top and bottom of the medallion are in light yellow and pink colours. Between the circles are flower patterns in light blue, and beyond them are red harlequin diapers. Yellow and green clouds show above the lotus leaves patterns on foot. The same clouds also show on the shoulder, and above them are four panels showing eight auspicious symbols of Buddhism between blue diapers and violet flowers.

creator: null

description: bowl, stoneware, celadon glaze with incised lotus petal decoration on outside, superb glaze and condition. This celadon glazed bowl has an incised decoration in low relief on the exterior. The triple layers of leaves are quickly cut and have slightly raised central ribs. The superb concentrated glaze heightens the relief pattern. The interior has been left plain. During firing in the kiln the dish was supported by four stilts, so that the celadon glaze could cover the base of the bowl. Carved to look like an opening lotus, this bowl demonstrates the Koryo love of forms and decoration inspired by nature. ( from Korean Gallery label copy)

description: Ginger jar; Made from porcelain, wood, and enamel paint. The jar has a circular opening and rounded shoulders, an ovoid body and a circular base. The jar has a wooden lid and stand carved like a seedpod with open work. The body of the jar is decorated with polychrome enamels showing four circular medallions of flowers, scholar wares and fo lion in a garden . Two half-floral decorations on the top and bottom of the medallion are in light yellow and pink colours. Between the circles are flower patterns in light blue, and beyond them are red harlequin diapers. Yellow and green clouds show above the lotus leaves patterns on foot. The same clouds also show on the shoulder, and above them are four panels showing eight auspicious symbols of Buddhism between blue diapers and violet flowers.

name: flask
creator: null
material: ceramic/inorganic material/AAT Materials; celadon/ceramic glaze/glaze/coating (material)/AAT Materials
description: flask, stoneware with celadon glaze bamboo type wall pattern, neck surmounted with pouring ring, light irregular glaze. This celadon glazed flask with a trumpet-shaped mouth has an unusual faceted-type wall pattern finishing with a repeated incised curve. In Korea potters were of a low status. They were not regarded as artists and records do not remain of the makers of pieces. Celadons were made as luxury goods exclusively for the royal family, the court and the aristocracy. Officials appointed by the court supervised the kilns. The kingfisher glaze was so highly prized that it has been recorded that only one pot out of ten made was selected. The rest were destroyed. The irregularity in the glaze, caused by the inability to maintain a reducing atmosphere in the kiln, is a variation on the requisite celadon coloration.( from Korean Gallery label copy)
material_tran: 陶瓷/无机材料/AAT材料；青瓷/陶瓷釉/釉料/涂层（材料）/AAT材料
description_tran: 烧瓶，瓷器青瓷竹制壁纹，颈上浇环，浅不规则釉。这只喇叭口青瓷釉瓶有一种不同寻常的刻面式壁纹，表面有重复的切割曲线。在韩国，陶工的地位很低。他们不被视为艺术家，作品制作者的记录也不存在。青瓷是专门为皇室、宫廷和贵族制作的奢侈品。朝廷任命的官员负责监督窑炉。翠鸟釉是如此珍贵，以至于有记录称，在制作的十个壶中只有一个被选中。其余的都被毁了。釉的不规则性是由于无法在窑中保持还原气氛而引起的，这是对必要的青瓷着色的一种变化。（来自韩国百宝箱标签副本）

description_tran: 圆形杯子，带茶碟，由中国古代瓷器制成，装饰有玫瑰家族的珐琅。装饰以崎岖的景观为特色，有房屋、岩石和鲜花。茶碟的内边缘由一条粉红色条纹和线条绘制的玫瑰花饰突出显示，四个保留区包含一朵花和叶子。杯子底部有一朵小花。

name: Assiette d'échantillon en porcelaine "coquille d'oeuf"
time: Chine ; dynastie Qing (1644-1911) (Chine) ; époque Yongzheng (1723-1735) (Chine->dynastie Qing (1644-1911)),vers 1730 - 1735
creator: Chine - atelier de Canton  ?
description: Une assiette d'échantillon en ancienne porcelaine de Chine, décor dit artistique. Dans le creux, deux coqs, des rochers et des fleurs. Au pourtour, un lambrequin bleu et noir, se détache d'une bordure à fond jaune rehaussée de quadrillages. Le marli, à rosaces dessinées au trait sur fond rose, présente trois réserves décorées de fruits et de fleurs et trois dragons en émail noir et or formant rosaces.
description_tran: 一个由中国古代瓷器制成的样品盘，所谓的艺术装饰。在洞里，两只公鸡，岩石和鲜花。在边缘，一条蓝色和黑色的lambrequin从黄色背景的边框上脱颖而出，边框上有网格。Marli以粉红色背景上的线条绘制的玫瑰花饰为特色，展示了三个装饰有水果和鲜花的储藏室，以及三条黑色珐琅和金色的龙，形成玫瑰花饰。

name: Assiette, d'une paire (R 1025 et 1026)Ancien titre
time: Chine ; dynastie Qing (1644-1911) (Chine) ; époque Qianlong (1736-1795) (Chine->dynastie Qing (1644-1911)),1740 - 1750
creator: Chine - atelier de Canton  ?
description: Sur le marli, décor bianco sopra bianco avec deux réserves historiées et une réserve comportant le monogramme CFB. Au centre, deux oiseaux sur des branches fleuries de pivoines. Présence d'un ancien décor doré effacé, visible à jour frisant, représentant des bambous. Décor posé lors de la fabrication de la pièce et de la pose du décor émaillé, retiré intentionnellement.Dans l'inventaire de la baronne Salomon de Rothschild, le monogramme CFB était identifié à celui de la comtesse Du Barry. Or la datation de l'assiette, selon des critères stylistiques, se situe au début des années 1740 et la comtesse Du Barry est née sans titre et sans fortune en 1743.Une assiette identique est conservée au Musée nationaldes Arts asiatiques-Guimet à Paris (inv. G4261).
description_tran: 在Marli上，Bianco Sopra Bianco装饰有两个历史保留区和一个带有CFB花押字的保留区。在中心，两只鸟在牡丹开花的树枝上。一个古老的褪色金色装饰的存在，在白天可以看到卷曲，代表竹子。在制作房间和铺设搪瓷装饰时铺设的装饰，有意移除。在萨洛蒙·德·罗斯柴尔德男爵夫人的库存中，CFB花押字被确定为杜巴里伯爵夫人的花押字。然而，根据风格标准，盘子的年代可以追溯到1740年代初，而杜巴里伯爵夫人在1743年出生时没有头衔，也没有财富。同样的盘子保存在巴黎的国家亚洲艺术博物馆-吉米特（inv.G4261）。

description: Sur le marli, décor bianco sopra bianco avec deux réserves historiées et une réserve comportant le monogramme CFB. Au centre, deux oiseaux sur des branches fleuries de pivoines. Présence d'un ancien décor doré effacé, visible à jour frisant, représentant des bambous. Décor posé lors de la fabrication de la pièce et de la pose du décor émaillé, retiré intentionnellement.Dans l'inventaire de la baronne Salomon de Rothschild, le monogramme CFB était identifié à celui de la comtesse Du Barry. Or la datation de l'assiette, selon des critères stylistiques, se situe au début des années 1740 et la comtesse Du Barry est née sans titre et sans fortune en 1743.Une assiette identique est conservée au Musée nationaldes Arts asiatiques-Guimet à Paris (inv. G4261).
description_tran: 在Marli上，Bianco Sopra Bianco装饰有两个历史保留区和一个带有CFB花押字的保留区。在中心，两只鸟在牡丹开花的树枝上。存在一个古老的褪色金色装饰，在白天可以看到卷曲，代表竹子。在制作房间和铺设搪瓷装饰时铺设的装饰，有意移除。在萨洛蒙·德·罗斯柴尔德男爵夫人的库存中，CFB花押字被确定为杜巴里伯爵夫人的花押字。然而，根据风格标准，盘子的年代可以追溯到1740年代初，而杜巴里伯爵夫人在1743年出生时没有头衔，也没有财富。同样的盘子保存在巴黎的国家亚洲艺术博物馆-吉米特（inv.G4261）。

description: Ce Crucifix provet du Brésil dérive d'un lointain modèle élaboré par Giambologna (1529-1608) -corps extrêmement gracile et allongé, périzonium couvrant les hanches en diagonale noué à dextre, visage vu de profil penché à dextre avec des mêches de cheveux glissant sur l'épaule. C'est une production des ateliers du sud de la Chine destinée à être exportée dans le monde entier, en activité depuis la fin du XVIe siècle.

description_tran: 欧洲夫妇Tet un rinceau doré-可能来自作为模型发送的雕刻，是1735-1740年生产的作品中反复出现的主题。例如，它可以在洛里昂印度公司博物馆（ML 387（1）C 192和ML 387（2）C 192）保存的一对带碟碗上找到。

name: Assiette
creator: Chine, atelier de Jingdezhen  ?
description: Au centre, deux femmes assises jouent avec deux enfants avec au premier plan un chat assis sur un fruit. La scène est entourée d'une bordure bleue et dorée polylobée. Sur le cavet se déploient une bande de rinceaux et de fleurs dorés, puis une bande rose à motifs losangés entrecoupée de réserves aux motifs stylisés. Sur le marli, des alvéoles octogonales roses sont semées de réserves blanches ornées de fleurs dorées et de dragons stylisés dans des médaillons. Enfin une dernière fine bande ornementale altert réserve et motifs verts, bleus et dorés enserre l'ensemble. Revers rubis.Le musée Smidt van Gelder à Anvers conserve une assiette identique à celle du Louvre (inv.SM.80/1-2) et une autre qui porte la même scène centrale mais avec système décoratif un peu différent (inv. SM.1694). Une seconde assiette identique à celle du Louvre se trouve dans les collections au British Museum à Londres (Franks.699.+.).
description_tran: 在中心，两个坐着的女人和两个孩子玩耍，前景是一只猫坐在水果上。场景被多叶蓝色和金色边框包围。酒窖上展开了一条金色的小花和花朵，然后是一条带有菱形图案的粉红色条纹，中间穿插着带有风格化图案的储备。在Marli上，粉红色的八角形肺泡点缀着白色的储备，装饰着金色的花朵和奖章中的风格化龙。最后，最后一条精细的Altert Reserve装饰带和绿色、蓝色和金色图案环绕着整个区域。安特卫普的斯密特·范·盖尔德博物馆（Smidt van Gelder Museum）保留了一个与卢浮宫相同的盘子（inv.SM.80/1-2），另一个盘子带有相同的中央舞台，但装饰系统略有不同（inv.SM.1694）。伦敦大英博物馆（Franks.699+）收藏了第二个与卢浮宫相同的盘子。

creator: Chine - atelier de Canton  Céramiste/potier, ?
size: Hauteur : 5 cm (maximum) ; Diamètre : 11,6 cm (maximum) ; Hauteur : 4 cm (tasse) ; Diamètre : 7 cm (tasse)
description: Au centre de la soucoupe et au fond de la tasse se trouve une main de bouddha dorée.Sur la soucoupe, cette main est inscrite au milieu d'un lotus sur fond blanc dont les six pétales forment des réserves aux pivoines et autres fleurs. Ces pétales se trouvent sur la face externe de la tasse. Ce décor s'achève par un fond diapré alterné vert et bleu semé d'une fleur rouge ou rose. Les contours du lotus et les rebords sont dorés.
creator_tran: 中国-广州陶艺家/陶艺家工作室，？
size_tran: 高度：5厘米（最大）；直径：11.6厘米（最大）；高度：4厘米（杯）；直径：7厘米（杯）
description_tran: 在茶碟的中心和杯子的底部是一只金佛手。在茶碟上，这只手刻在白色背景上的莲花中间，莲花的六片花瓣为牡丹和其他花提供了储备。这些花瓣位于杯子的外表面。这一装饰以绿色和蓝色交替的透明背景结束，背景上点缀着红色或粉红色的花朵。莲花的轮廓和边缘是金色的。

name: Tasse et soucoupe

description: Tasse et soucoupe à fond rose et réserves fleuries sur fond maté. V1301 A et B et VDN407 A et B).

description_tran: 粉红色背景的杯子和茶碟，哑光背景上的花卉储备。中心是位于米德尔堡和阿姆斯特丹的荷兰家族Van Fernij的纹章。布鲁塞尔皇家艺术和历史博物馆（inv.V1301 a和B以及VDN407 a和B）保存了一个茶壶和一个杯子及其碟式公寓。

description: Tasse et soucoupe sont ornées de réserves sur fond blanc dans lesquelles des hommes devisent au bord d'une rivière. La scène est encadrée par une bordure dorée formée de quatre chauves-souris. Le marli et les parois extérieures de la tasse sont ornés d'un décor bianco sopra bianco semé d'une alterce de réserves rondes émaillées de noir ou quadrilobées émaillées de rose.

description: Décor géométrique losangé et réserves à pivoines et chrysanthèmes ou à armoiries. Les armoiries ont été dans un premier temps identifiées à l'anglais Morris de Caernarvon puis à la famille Jones "de Monmouth" par analogie avec un ex-libris daté vers 1725 (cf. D. S. Howard, Chinese Armorial Porcelain, Londres, 1974, p. 232, et idem, Londres, 2003, vol. II, p. 155).
size_tran: 高度：11.2厘米（最大）；长度：16.5厘米（最大）；宽度：10厘米（最大）；高度：8厘米（茶壶）；高度：4厘米（盖子）；直径：6.2厘米（盖子）
description_tran: 菱形几何装饰和牡丹和菊花或盾形纹章的储备。这些纹章最初被认定为英国人莫里斯·德·卡纳冯（Morris de Caernarvon），后来被认定为“蒙茅斯”的琼斯家族，类似于1725年左右的藏书板（参见D.S.霍华德，《中国纹章瓷器》，伦敦，1974年，第232页，同上，伦敦，2003年，第二卷，第155页）。

name: Assiette d'échantillon
time: Chine ; dynastie Qing (1644-1911) (Chine) ; époque Yongzheng (1723-1735) (Chine->dynastie Qing (1644-1911)),vers 1730 (bibliographie/travail de référence)
creator: Chine, atelier de Jingdezhen  ?, bibliographie/travail de référence
description: Dans le creux de l'assiette est représentée une jeune femme jouant avec trois enfants. Le marli est décoré sur fond de motifs hexagonaux alternés de petits carrés de trois réserves à fleurs et de trois armoriées. Le dessous de l'assiette, sauf le milieu circulaire resté blanc, est couleur rubis.Dans l'inventaire de la collection d'Adolphe Thiers, Charles Blanc désigne cette assiette, ainsi qu'une autre semblable (TH 536), comme étant des "assiettes d'échantillon", c'est-à-dire des prototypes destinés à être montrés aux éventuels commanditaires.
creator_tran: 中国，景德镇车间？，参考书目/参考作品
description_tran: 盘子的中空处描绘了一位年轻女子与三个孩子玩耍。Marli以六边形图案为背景，交替使用三个花卉储备和三个盔甲的小正方形。除了保持白色的圆形介质外，盘子的底部是红宝石色的。在阿道夫·泰尔斯收藏的库存中，查尔斯·布兰克将这个盘子和另一个类似的盘子（TH 536）称为“样品盘子”，即向潜在赞助商展示的原型。

description: Vase en forme de carafe, à panse sphérique et à col long légèrement évasé, fond bleu fouetté et à quatre réserves de fleurs décoratives en émaux de la famille verte. Ils sont garnis de montures en bronze doré.
description_tran: 水瓶形状的花瓶，球形，略微张开的长颈，鲜艳的蓝色背景，四个装饰性的绿色家族珐琅花储备。它们装饰有镀金青铜框架。

name: Tasse à thé et soucoupe d'un ensemble de trois (TH 505 à 507)
time: Chine ; dynastie Qing (1644-1911) (Chine) ; époque Qianlong (1736-1795) (Chine->dynastie Qing (1644-1911)),vers 1750 - 1760
creator: Chine - atelier de Canton  ?
type: art de la table ; tasse et soucoupe
size: Hauteur : 5,1 cm (Max) ; Diamètre : 13,6 cm (Max) ; Hauteur : 4,4 cm (tasse) ; Diamètre : 8,6 cm (tasse) ; Hauteur de l'accessoire : 2,2 cm (Soucoupe)
description: Le décor consiste, sur les bords du marli des soucoupes et sur les bords internes des tasses, en une bande géométrique bleu clair interrompue par des fleurs roses. Sur la soucoupe et l'extérieur de la tasse, se développent quatre réserves avec des pivoines aux contours émaillés de bleu reliées par un motif représentant des vases noirs rehaussés d'or avec des pivoines sur un fonds rose . Enfin, au centre de la soucoupe et de la tasse, se trouve un vase bleu posé sur un socle rouge entouré de pivoines, d'une fleurs blanche et d'ornements. Dans le vase, une plume de paon et ce qui pourrait être un champignon lingzhi, symbole de longévité.

description_tran: 装饰包括在茶碟的marli边缘和杯子的内边缘，一条浅蓝色的几何条纹被粉红色的花朵打断。在茶碟和杯子的外部，有四个带有牡丹的储藏室，蓝色珐琅轮廓由一个图案连接，该图案代表黑色花瓶，粉红色背景上用牡丹装饰金色。最后，在茶碟和杯子的中心，有一个蓝色花瓶放在红色底座上，周围是牡丹、白花和装饰品。花瓶里有孔雀羽毛，可能是灵芝蘑菇，长寿的象征。

name: Tasse à thé et soucoupe d'un ensemble de trois (TH 505 à 507)
time: Chine ; dynastie Qing (1644-1911) (Chine) ; époque Qianlong (1736-1795) (Chine->dynastie Qing (1644-1911)),vers 1750 - 1760
creator: Chine - atelier de Canton  ?
type: art de la table ; tasse et soucoupe
size: Diamètre : 13,7 cm (soucoupe) ; Diamètre : 8,7 cm (tasse) ; Hauteur : 4,3 cm (tasse)
description: Le décor consiste, sur les bords du marli des soucoupes et sur les bords internes des tasses, en une bande géométrique bleu clair interrompue par des fleurs roses. Sur la soucoupe et l'extérieur de la tasse, se développent quatre réserves avec des pivoines aux contours émaillés de bleu reliées par un motif représentant des vases noirs rehaussés d'or avec des pivoines sur un fonds rose . Enfin, au centre de la soucoupe et de la tasse, se trouve un vase bleu posé sur un socle rouge entouré de pivoines, d'une fleurs blanche et d'ornements. Dans le vase, une plume de paon et ce qui pourrait être un champignon lingzhi, symbole de longévité.

name: Bol à lèvre en porcelaine "coquille d'oeuf"
time: Chine ; dynastie Qing (1644-1911) (Chine) ; époque Yongzheng (1723-1735) (Chine->dynastie Qing (1644-1911)),vers 1730 - 1740
creator: Chine - atelier de Canton  ?
description: Emaux de la famille rose. A l'extérieur, une poule et ses poussins et deux coq qui se battent. Deux autres coqs marchent, parmi des pivoines et des chrysanthèmes sur un terrain accidenté. L'intérieur est orné d'un bouquet de pivoines et de fruits tel le citron Main de Bouddha, porte-bonheur en Asie, et le marli, de trois compartiments réservés avec des fleurs et reliés entre eux par des motifs alvéolés.
description_tran: 罗斯家族的电子邮件。外面，一只母鸡和小鸡，两只公鸡在打架。另外两只公鸡在崎岖的地形上，在牡丹和菊花中行走。内部装饰有一束牡丹和水果，如佛陀之手柠檬（亚洲的幸运符）和马利（marli），三个隔间保留有鲜花，并通过蜂窝图案连接在一起。

name: Vase de section carrée
creator: Chine, atelier de Jingdezhen  Céramiste/potier
size: Hauteur : 29,5 cm (max) ; Longueur : 10 cm (max) ; Largeur : 9,9 cm (max) ; Hauteur : 24,7 cm (vase) ; Longueur : 9 cm (vase) ; Largeur : 8 cm (vase) ; Hauteur : 6,9 cm (base)
description: Le vase est décoré de figures et de fleurs en émaux de la famille verte et est présenté sur un socle mobile. Deux faces sont ornées de scènes : un enfant et une jeune femme conduisent un vieillard qui s'appuie sur l'épaule de l'enfant et deux personnages devisent devant une barrière. Les deux autres faces sont décorées de branches fleuries. Sur la panse se déploient deux dragons en ronde-bosse. En haut et en bas, se trouve une bordure en mosaïque verte jaspée, avec fleurs roses au milieu.

name: Brûle-parfum porté par trois figures de chinois
creator: Chine
material: cuivre (doré),bronze (anses, personnages formant les 3 pieds, bouton central du couvercle)
description: Le pot de forme sphéroïde est en cuivre doré et porte en guise de anses quatre anneaux en bronze tenus chacun par une tête de lion de Fo. Il est supporté par trois figures de chinois, en bronze également, très vivantes et très animées et il est fermé par un couvercle dont le centre est un gros bouton en bronze ajouré. L'ensemble est décoré d'émaux cloisonnés: des fleurs sur fond noir tout autour de la panse (fleurs de cerisier, lotus, chrysanthème...) et sur le couvercle deux lions chimériques sur fond bleu.

description_tran: 这个球形的罐子由镀金铜制成，有四个青铜环作为把手，每个环由一个狮子头固定。它由三个中国人像支撑，也是青铜人像，非常活泼，非常活泼。它由一个盖子封闭，盖子的中心是一个大的穿孔青铜按钮。整个装饰有分隔的珐琅：黑色背景上的花围绕着臀部（樱花、莲花、菊花……），盖子上有两个蓝色背景上的嵌合狮子。

name: Plateau à six pans, d'un service (R 1019, 1198, 1199, 1204, 1206 et 1207)
creator: null
type: art de la table ; soucoupe ; plateau
description: Plateau à six pans, peut-être pour poser la théière R 1198. La scène historiée au centre représente une jeune femme assise sur un tapis en train de prendre le thé. Devant elle, un domestique agenouillé lui sert la boisson et derrière, une servante l'évente à l'aide d'un écran à longue tige. La scène est cernée par une bordure d'ornements dorés et les bords sont tapissés de fins rinceaux dorés semés de réserves ovales ou quadrilobées ornées d'un décor végétal ou d'un paysage
description_tran: 六角托盘，可能用于放置茶壶R 1198。中心的历史场景描绘了一位年轻女子坐在地毯上喝茶。在她面前，一个跪着的仆人为她端上饮料，在她身后，一个女仆用一个长长的屏风吹着她。场景周围是金色装饰物的边缘，边缘覆盖着精细的金色卷轴，卷轴上点缀着椭圆形或四叶形的保护区，装饰着植物装饰或景观。

name: Tête de femme
creator: Anonyme  Ivoirier
placeOfOrigin: Chine du sud = sud de la Chine (Asie->Asie orientale = Extrême Orient)
size: Hauteur : 11,7 cm ; Largeur : 7,3 cm ; Profondeur : 4,2 cm
description: Le visage carré, assez lourd, est encadré de mèches parallèles rehaussées de polychromie, comme les yeux et les lèvres, ce qui la rattache aux ivoires de Chine méridionale produits pour le marché espagnol. Il s'agit d'un haut-relief, et la sculpture s'interrompt brutalement à l'arrière. La taille en bouchon du cou la désigne comme un élément destiné à être encastré dans un corps fabriqué dans un autre matériau, dans la tradition directe d'une pratique hispanique "por vestir", à habiller, où les parties de chair visibles sont sculptées et peintes tandis que le reste du corps est un simple mannequin vêtu.
placeOfOrigin_tran: 中国南部=中国南部（亚洲->东亚=远东）
size_tran: 高度：11.7厘米；宽度：7.3厘米；深度：4.2厘米
description_tran: 方形的脸相当重，由平行的多色增强灯芯构成，如眼睛和嘴唇，这将其与为西班牙市场生产的南中国象牙联系起来。这是一个高浮雕，雕塑在后面突然停止。颈部的帽状尺寸将其指定为一个元素，旨在嵌入由另一种材料制成的身体中，这是西班牙裔“por vestir”的直接传统，即穿衣，其中可见的身体部位被雕刻和绘制，而身体的其余部分是一个简单的穿衣人体模型。

name: Perroquet, d'une paire

description: Perroquet en porcelaine de Chine bleue céleste sur un socle en bronze doré. Se trouvait en 1789 dans le Cabinet intérieur de Marie-Antoinette à Versailles puis confié au marchand Dominique Daguerre, puis Martin Lignereux ; en 1793 entre dans les collections nationales ; château des Tuileries en 1833 (appartement du duc d'Orléans), puis jusqu'en 1870 château de Saint-Cloud ; à cette date dans les collections du Louvre.

creator: null

description: Perroquet en porcelaine de Chine bleue céleste sur un socle en bronze doré. Se trouvait en 1789 dans le Cabinet intérieur de Marie-Antoinette à Versailles puis confié au marchand Dominique Daguerre, puis Martin Lignereux ; en 1793 entre dans les collections nationales ; château des Tuileries en 1833 (appartement du duc d'Orléans), puis jusqu'en 1870 château de Saint-Cloud ; à cette date dans les collections du Louvre.

description_tran: 金色青铜底座上的天蓝色中国鹦鹉。1789年，他在凡尔赛宫的玛丽·安托瓦内特（Marie Antoinette）的内室里，然后被委托给商人多米尼克·达盖尔（Dominique Daguerre），然后是马丁·利内鲁（Martin Lignereux）；1793年进入国家收藏；1833年的杜伊勒里城堡（奥尔良公爵的公寓），直到1870年的圣克劳德城堡；在卢浮宫收藏的这一天。

name: Rouleau
creator: Anonyme
type: art du livre : calligraphie ; art du livre : dessin, page d'album
description: Rouleau chinois peint sur soie, représentant un haras avec ses chevaux, et portant de longues inscriptions en gros caractères développant l'histoire d'un empereur chinois qui s'occupa d'améliorer par des croisements la race de ces chevaux.Rien de plus naturel que le tableau du haras impérial ; les étalons y sont peints à l'aquarelle dans les attitudes les plus variées et les plus vraies : celui-ci raclant le sol avec la pointe de son sabot, celui-là se grattant l'oreille, quelques-uns vus de croupe ou de face, dans les raccourcis les plus difficiles à saisir.Plus loin, en allant de droite à gauche, comme l'on fait pour lire les écritures chinoises, on voit venir un amateur de distinction à qui le directeur du haras, assez simplement vêtu, montre ses écuries.Les chevaux peints dans ce rouleau sont huit étalons célèbres qui ont été chantés par le poète Li-Thai-Po.
type_tran: 书籍艺术：书法；书籍艺术：绘画、相册页
description_tran: 一幅中国卷轴，画在丝绸上，描绘了一个种马场和他的马，上面有长长的大字铭文，讲述了一位中国皇帝的故事，他致力于通过杂交来改善这些马的品种。没有什么比帝国种马场的画作更自然的了；在那里，种马以最真实和多样的姿势被水彩画：一匹用蹄尖刮地，一匹抓耳朵，有些是从臀部或前面看到的，在最难抓住的捷径上。再往前走，从右到左，就像阅读中国经文一样，你会看到一位杰出的业余爱好者，种马场的主管穿着简单，向他展示了他的马厩。这幅卷轴上描绘的马是诗人李泰波演唱的八匹著名种马。

name: Vase à huit pans et à couvercle, d'une paire (TH 480)
creator: null
description: Potiche à huit pans et à couvercle décorée en émaux de la famille rose. Les huit faces sont ornées par alterce de plantes fleuries et de personnages. L'arbuste planté sur une face se tord pour aller fleurir sur l'autre. Les figures appartiennent au genre familier. Une femme, à la fenêtre d'un pavillon de jardin, salue un personnage bien mis qui passe au pied du pavillon. Une jeune fille tient dans ses bras un lapin blanc. Deux autres offrent des fruits à un perroquet sur son perchoir. Sur es huit pans du col, des figurines alternent avec des animaux aquatiques, carpes roses, écrevisses, crabes. Les deux potiches se font pendant.
description_tran: 八面和盖子的potiche装饰有玫瑰家族的珐琅。八张脸上装饰着花卉植物和人物。种植在一面的灌木扭曲，在另一面开花。这些人物属于熟悉的类型。一个女人站在花园亭子的窗户前，向一个从亭子脚下走过的穿着得体的人致意。一个年轻女孩抱着一只白兔。另外两个在鹦鹉的栖息处提供水果。在颈部的八个部分，雕像与水生动物、粉红鲤鱼、小龙虾和螃蟹交替出现。这两个potiches是同时进行的。

name: Vase ou potiche
creator: Anonyme
description: Grande potiche couverte décorée en émaux de la famille rose. Elle offre au pourtour de la panse de grandes figures de divinités vêtues de riches costumes et placées chacune sur des feuilles de plantes marines nageant sur les flots. Le bord supérieur ainsi que la partie supérieure de la panse présentent des fleurs et des lambrequins.
description_tran: 用玫瑰家族的珐琅装饰的大型有盖potiche。它在腹股沟周围提供了穿着丰富服装的大型神灵形象，每个人都被放置在漂浮在水面上的海洋植物的叶子上。顶部边缘和顶部腹部有花和羔羊。

name: Vase à huit pans et à couvercle, d'une paire (TH 479)
creator: null
description: Potiche à huit pans et à couvercle décorée en émaux de la famille rose. Les huit faces sont ornées par alterce de plantes fleuries et de personnages. L'arbuste planté sur une face se tord pour aller fleurir sur l'autre. Les figures appartiennent au genre familier. Une femme, à la fenêtre d'un pavillon de jardin, salue un personnage bien mis qui passe au pied du pavillon. Une jeune fille tient dans ses bras un lapin blanc. Deux autres offrent des fruits à un perroquet sur son perchoir. Sur es huit pans du col, des figurines alternent avec des animaux aquatiques, carpes roses, écrevisses, crabes. Les deux potiches se font pendant.
description_tran: 八面和盖子的potiche装饰有玫瑰家族的珐琅。八张脸上装饰着花卉植物和人物。种植在一面的灌木扭曲，在另一面开花。这些人物属于熟悉的类型。一个女人站在花园亭子的窗户前，向一个从亭子脚下走过的穿着得体的人致意。一个年轻女孩抱着一只白兔。另外两个在鹦鹉的栖息处提供水果。在颈部的八个部分，雕像与水生动物、粉红鲤鱼、小龙虾和螃蟹交替出现。这两个potiches是同时进行的。

name: 旟鼎
creator: 无
placeOfOrigin: 1972年眉县杨家村铜器窖藏出土
size: 通高77厘米，口径56.5厘米，重78.5公斤
description:
内壁共铸铭文四行，28字，大意是说：某年八月初，王姜将原赐予师栌的土地收回，转赐给旟，旟便做此鼎纪念。铭文反映了“普天之下，莫非王土；率土之滨，莫非王臣”的土地占有制形态。承袭商代圆鼎风格，造型厚重庄严，纹饰十分精美，口沿下方饰有兽面纹，以雷纹为底纹（雷纹是一种带有方折角的回旋曲线）。
西周时期，统治者为了巩固政权，实行分封制，将人民和疆土，分封给各诸侯国，周天子是最高的土地所有者，可以将土地和耕种土地的人，任意赐给他的下属，也有权将土地收回，其臣属对君王所赐的土地只有使用权而没有所有权。旟鼎内壁的铭文是研究西周初期土地制度的重要资料，具有珍贵的历史及艺术价值，同时铭文铸刻时代明确，被公认为周康王时的断代标准器。

name: 独孤信多面体煤精组印
creator: 无
description:
这枚印章是由26个大小不一的正方形和三角形组成的多面体，其中14个正方形印面上刻着规范的楷书阴文。印章由煤精刻制而成，煤精也称煤玉，是褐煤的一种变种，以低等植物为主，也有部分高等植物遗体组成的腐植腐泥混合煤。这枚印章的主人是西魏八柱国之一、鲜卑族上层人物独孤信，原名独孤如愿。
印文的内容可分为三大类：公文用印，如“大都督印”、“大司马印”、“柱国之印”、“令”、“密”等；上书用印，如“臣信上疏”、“臣信上章”等；书简用印，如“独孤信白书”、“信启事”等。多面体印章使得这位身兼数职的独孤信使用起来十分方便。独孤信不仅自身战功赫赫，他的女儿也很有名。他有7个女儿，其中大女儿嫁给了北周的明帝，成为周明敬后；七女儿嫁给了隋开国皇帝杨坚，是历史上以嫉妒著称的隋文献后；四女儿嫁给了唐代开国皇帝李渊的父亲。因此他作了连续三个朝代的国丈或太上国丈，所以人们戏称他为“中国古代第一老丈人”。不过正因为有此渊源，所以隋唐两代最高统治者身上都流淌有少数民族的血液，因此大唐盛世吸纳各方精髓、接受异族文化就没有太多的心理障碍，这也成为隋唐两代社会开放、民族平等的前提之一。

name: 多友鼎
creator: 无
size: 通高51.5厘米，口径50厘米，腹深31厘米，重35千克
description:
青铜器发展到西周中晚期，形制逐渐趋向定制，尤其在进入晚期以后，各类铜器都进入了整齐划一的时代。以青铜鼎为例，这一时期的青铜鼎主要只有两种形制。一种是克鼎类，主要特征是盆形体，腹宽大而呈扁体形，蹄足上部一般有兽面装饰，装饰纹样一般为环带纹和窃曲纹，散伯车父鼎属于此类；另一种为毛公鼎形，主要以半球形体、蹄足为特征，装饰纹样简单，一般仅以弦纹、重环纹或窃曲纹装饰，多友鼎就属于这一类。
多友鼎，半球形体，器腹较深，蹄足。装饰花纹简单，仅在器腹上部装饰两道弦纹。器内壁有铭文二百七十余字，是建国以来陕西地区出土铭文最多的青铜器之一。铭文记载的是西周厉王时期与猃狁的一场战争。猃狁此次入侵危及京畿腹地，厉王命令武公派遣多友率兵迎击，激战半个月，先后在采阝、龚、世、杨冢等地战斗，共打了四次大仗，都取得了胜利。杀掉敌军三百余人，俘获二十多人，缴获战车一百二十七辆，夺回了被掳去的人民，将猃狁逐出了周境。武公将多友的战绩报告给了厉王，厉王给予以多友重赏，赐给多友青铜一百多钧。多友特铸此鼎以纪念这件事情。
西周晚期的青铜器铭文，许多都记载着周人反击猃狁的事件。猃狁是西周时期北方地区重要的民族之一，与西周王朝经常发生战争。当时的猃狁是西北主要的边患，时常侵扰周，劫掠财物、人口，严重威胁着周王朝的统治。
在铭文中涉及到猃狁的铜器中，多友鼎是最为重要的一件。这篇铭文对战争的原因、过程以及结果都进行了详细的介绍。这些资料对研究西周晚期的历史、西周晚期同北方少数民族的关系及古文字研究、历史地理研究等都有重要的参考价值。
